{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I believe that there are new, hidden tensions"},{"time":4000,"text":"that are actually happening between people and institutions --"},{"time":7000,"text":"institutions that are the institutions that people"},{"time":9000,"text":"inhabit in their daily life:"},{"time":11000,"text":"schools, hospitals, workplaces,"},{"time":14000,"text":"factories, offices, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17000,"text":"And something that I see happening"},{"time":20000,"text":"is something that I would like to call"},{"time":22000,"text":"a sort of \"democratization of intimacy.\""},{"time":24000,"text":"And what do I mean by that?"},{"time":26000,"text":"I mean that what people are doing"},{"time":28000,"text":"is, in fact, they are sort of, with their communication channels,"},{"time":32000,"text":"they are breaking an imposed isolation"},{"time":36000,"text":"that these institutions are imposing on them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"How are they doing this? They're doing it"},{"time":42000,"text":"in a very simple way, by calling their mom from work,"},{"time":44000,"text":"by IMing from their office to their friends,"},{"time":48000,"text":"by texting under the desk."},{"time":50000,"text":"The pictures that you're seeing behind me"},{"time":52000,"text":"are people that I visited in the last few months."},{"time":55000,"text":"And I asked them to come along with the person they communicate with most."},{"time":59000,"text":"And somebody brought a boyfriend, somebody a father."},{"time":62000,"text":"One young woman brought her grandfather."},{"time":65000,"text":"For 20 years, I've been looking at how people use"},{"time":67000,"text":"channels such as email, the mobile phone, texting, etc."},{"time":71000,"text":"What we're actually going to see is that, fundamentally,"},{"time":73000,"text":"people are communicating on a regular basis"},{"time":76000,"text":"with five, six, seven of their most intimate sphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80000,"text":"Now, lets take some data. Facebook."},{"time":82000,"text":"Recently some sociologists from Facebook --"},{"time":84000,"text":"Facebook is the channel that you would expect"},{"time":86000,"text":"is the most enlargening of all channels."},{"time":89000,"text":"And an average user,"},{"time":91000,"text":"said Cameron Marlow,"},{"time":94000,"text":"from Facebook, has about 120 friends."},{"time":97000,"text":"But he actually talks to,"},{"time":99000,"text":"has two-way exchanges with, about four to six people"},{"time":102000,"text":"on a regular base, depending on his gender."},{"time":104000,"text":"Academic research on instant messaging"},{"time":106000,"text":"also shows 100 people on buddy lists,"},{"time":109000,"text":"but fundamentally people chat with two, three, four --"},{"time":112000,"text":"anyway, less than five."},{"time":114000,"text":"My own research on cellphones and voice calls"},{"time":118000,"text":"shows that 80 percent of the calls"},{"time":120000,"text":"are actually made to four people. 80 percent."},{"time":123000,"text":"And when you go to Skype, it's down to two people."},{"time":126000,"text":"A lot of sociologists actually are quite disappointed."},{"time":128000,"text":"I mean, I've been a bit disappointed sometimes"},{"time":131000,"text":"when I saw this data and all this deployment, just for five people."},{"time":135000,"text":"And some sociologists actually feel that"},{"time":137000,"text":"it's a closure, it's a cocooning,"},{"time":142000,"text":"that we're disengaging from the public."},{"time":144000,"text":"And I would actually, I would like to show you that"},{"time":146000,"text":"if we actually look at who is doing it,"},{"time":148000,"text":"and from where they're doing it,"},{"time":150000,"text":"actually there is an incredible social transformation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"There are three stories that I think are quite good examples."},{"time":155000,"text":"The first gentleman, he's a baker."},{"time":157000,"text":"And so he starts working every morning at four o'clock in the morning."},{"time":160000,"text":"And around eight o'clock he sort of sneaks away from his oven,"},{"time":163000,"text":"cleans his hands from the flour"},{"time":165000,"text":"and calls his wife."},{"time":167000,"text":"He just wants to wish her a good day, because that's the start of her day."},{"time":170000,"text":"And I've heard this story a number of times."},{"time":173000,"text":"A young factory worker who works night shifts,"},{"time":176000,"text":"who manages to sneak away from the factory floor,"},{"time":179000,"text":"where there is CCTV by the way,"},{"time":181000,"text":"and find a corner, where at 11 o'clock at night"},{"time":183000,"text":"he can call his girlfriend and just say goodnight."},{"time":186000,"text":"Or a mother who, at four o'clock,"},{"time":188000,"text":"suddenly manages to find a corner in the toilet"},{"time":191000,"text":"to check that her children are safely home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195000,"text":"Then there is another couple, there is a Brazilian couple."},{"time":197000,"text":"They've lived in Italy for a number of years."},{"time":199000,"text":"They Skype with their families a few times a week."},{"time":202000,"text":"But once a fortnight, they actually put the computer on their dining table,"},{"time":206000,"text":"pull out the webcam and actually have dinner"},{"time":208000,"text":"with their family in Sao Paulo. And they have a big event of it."},{"time":211000,"text":"And I heard this story the first time a couple of years ago"},{"time":214000,"text":"from a very modest family"},{"time":216000,"text":"of immigrants from Kosovo in Switzerland."},{"time":219000,"text":"They had set up a big screen in their living room,"},{"time":222000,"text":"and every morning they had breakfast with their grandmother."},{"time":225000,"text":"But Danny Miller, who is a very good anthropologist"},{"time":228000,"text":"who is working on Filipina migrant women"},{"time":233000,"text":"who leave their children back in the Philippines,"},{"time":236000,"text":"was telling me about how much parenting is going on"},{"time":239000,"text":"through Skype,"},{"time":241000,"text":"and how much these mothers are engaged with their children through Skype."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245000,"text":"And then there is the third couple. They are two friends."},{"time":248000,"text":"They chat to each other every day, a few times a day actually."},{"time":252000,"text":"And finally, finally, they've managed to put"},{"time":254000,"text":"instant messaging on their computers at work."},{"time":256000,"text":"And now, obviously, they have it open."},{"time":258000,"text":"Whenever they have a moment they chat to each other."},{"time":260000,"text":"And this is exactly what we've been seeing"},{"time":262000,"text":"with teenagers and kids doing it in school, under the table,"},{"time":265000,"text":"and texting under the table to their friends."},{"time":268000,"text":"So, none of these cases are unique."},{"time":270000,"text":"I mean, I could tell you hundreds of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"But what is really exceptional is the setting."},{"time":275000,"text":"So, think of the three settings I've talked to you about:"},{"time":278000,"text":"factory, migration, office."},{"time":281000,"text":"But it could be in a school, it could be an administration,"},{"time":284000,"text":"it could be a hospital."},{"time":286000,"text":"Three settings that, if we just step back 15 years,"},{"time":288000,"text":"if you just think back 15 years,"},{"time":291000,"text":"when you clocked in,"},{"time":293000,"text":"when you clocked in to an office,"},{"time":295000,"text":"when you clocked in to a factory,"},{"time":297000,"text":"there was no contact for the whole duration of the time,"},{"time":300000,"text":"there was no contact with your private sphere."},{"time":303000,"text":"If you were lucky there was a public phone hanging in the corridor or somewhere."},{"time":307000,"text":"If you were in management, oh, that was a different story."},{"time":310000,"text":"Maybe you had a direct line."},{"time":312000,"text":"If you were not, you maybe had to go through an operator."},{"time":315000,"text":"But basically, when you walked into those buildings,"},{"time":318000,"text":"the private sphere was left behind you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321000,"text":"And this has become such a norm of our professional lives,"},{"time":326000,"text":"such a norm and such an expectation."},{"time":328000,"text":"And it had nothing to do with technical capability."},{"time":331000,"text":"The phones were there. But the expectation was once you moved in there"},{"time":334000,"text":"your commitment was fully to the task at hand,"},{"time":337000,"text":"fully to the people around you."},{"time":340000,"text":"That was where the focus had to be."},{"time":342000,"text":"And this has become such a cultural norm"},{"time":345000,"text":"that we actually school our children for them to be capable to do this cleavage."},{"time":349000,"text":"If you think nursery, kindergarten, first years of school"},{"time":351000,"text":"are just dedicated to take away the children,"},{"time":354000,"text":"to make them used to staying long hours away from their family."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"And then the school enacts perfectly well."},{"time":360000,"text":"It mimics perfectly all the rituals that we will find in offices:"},{"time":363000,"text":"rituals of entry, rituals of exit,"},{"time":366000,"text":"the schedules, the uniforms in this country,"},{"time":370000,"text":"things that identify you, team-building activities,"},{"time":373000,"text":"team building that will allow you to basically"},{"time":376000,"text":"be with a random group of kids, or a random group of people"},{"time":379000,"text":"that you will have to be with for a number of time."},{"time":382000,"text":"And of course, the major thing:"},{"time":384000,"text":"learn to pay attention,"},{"time":386000,"text":"to concentrate and focus your attention."},{"time":389000,"text":"This only started about 150 years ago."},{"time":391000,"text":"It only started with the birth of modern bureaucracy,"},{"time":394000,"text":"and of industrial revolution."},{"time":396000,"text":"When people basically had to go somewhere else to work"},{"time":399000,"text":"and carry out the work."},{"time":401000,"text":"And when with modern bureaucracy there was a very rational approach,"},{"time":404000,"text":"where there was a clear distinction between the private sphere"},{"time":406000,"text":"and the public sphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408000,"text":"So, until then, basically people were living on top of their trades."},{"time":412000,"text":"They were living on top of the land they were laboring."},{"time":415000,"text":"They were living on top of the workshops where they were working."},{"time":418000,"text":"And if you think, it's permeated our whole culture,"},{"time":420000,"text":"even our cities."},{"time":422000,"text":"If you think of medieval cities, medieval cities the boroughs"},{"time":425000,"text":"all have the names of the guilds and professions that lived there."},{"time":428000,"text":"Now we have sprawling residential suburbias"},{"time":431000,"text":"that are well distinct from production areas"},{"time":434000,"text":"and commercial areas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437000,"text":"And actually, over these 150 years,"},{"time":439000,"text":"there has been a very clear class system that also has emerged."},{"time":442000,"text":"So the lower the status of the job"},{"time":446000,"text":"and of the person carrying out, the more removed"},{"time":448000,"text":"he would be from his personal sphere."},{"time":451000,"text":"People have taken this amazing possibility"},{"time":454000,"text":"of actually being in contact all through the day"},{"time":456000,"text":"or in all types of situations."},{"time":458000,"text":"And they are doing it massively."},{"time":460000,"text":"The Pew Institute, which produces good data"},{"time":462000,"text":"on a regular basis on, for instance, in the States,"},{"time":465000,"text":"says that -- and I think that this number is conservative --"},{"time":467000,"text":"50 percent of anybody with email access at work"},{"time":471000,"text":"is actually doing private email from his office."},{"time":474000,"text":"I really think that the number is conservative."},{"time":478000,"text":"In my own research, we saw that the peak for private email"},{"time":480000,"text":"is actually 11 o'clock in the morning, whatever the country."},{"time":484000,"text":"75 percent of people admit doing private"},{"time":487000,"text":"conversations from work on their mobile phones."},{"time":490000,"text":"100 percent are using text."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493000,"text":"The point is that this re-appropriation of the personal sphere"},{"time":497000,"text":"is not terribly successful with all institutions."},{"time":500000,"text":"I'm always surprised the U.S. Army"},{"time":502000,"text":"sociologists are discussing of the impact"},{"time":504000,"text":"for instance, of soldiers in Iraq"},{"time":506000,"text":"having daily contact with their families."},{"time":509000,"text":"But there are many institutions that are actually blocking this access."},{"time":515000,"text":"And every day, every single day,"},{"time":517000,"text":"I read news that makes me cringe,"},{"time":519000,"text":"like a $15 fine"},{"time":521000,"text":"to kids in Texas,"},{"time":523000,"text":"for using, every time they take out their mobile phone in school."},{"time":526000,"text":"Immediate dismissal to bus drivers in New York,"},{"time":530000,"text":"if seen with a mobile phone in a hand."},{"time":532000,"text":"Companies blocking access to IM or to Facebook."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538000,"text":"Behind issues of security and safety,"},{"time":541000,"text":"which have always been the arguments for social control,"},{"time":544000,"text":"in fact what is going on is that"},{"time":546000,"text":"these institutions are trying to decide"},{"time":550000,"text":"who, in fact, has a right to self determine their attention,"},{"time":553000,"text":"to decide, whether they should, or not, be isolated."},{"time":557000,"text":"And they are actually trying to block, in a certain sense,"},{"time":563000,"text":"this movement of a greater possibility of intimacy."}]}]}